header.gameNote: LAS VEGAS INVITATIONAL AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: Tennessee State 49, Towson State 47
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Senior forward Clarence Matthews had 14 points, eight rebounds and a career high five blocks including two in the final seven seconds to lift Tennessee State past Towson State 49-47 Saturday afternoon in the final round of the Las Vegas Invitational. LaDarious Weaver added 13 points for Tennessee State (2-2), and Larry Turner had eight points and 14 rebounds in the eight-team round-robin tournament. In the final seconds, Matthews blocked C.C. Williams' and Winstonn Tubbs' shots in the lane that could have given Towson State the lead. Matthews grabbed the rebound and passed to Weaver, who was fouled with 2.3 seconds left. He hit the first free throw, but missed the second. Off the rebound, Gary Neal's desperation 3-pointer from halftime did not draw iron. Neal and Williams led Towson State (3-3) with 10 points apiece. Dennard Abraham had seven points and 13 rebounds for Towson State. Towson State built a 47-43 lead with 2:46 left before Tennessee State went on a 6-0 run to end it, highlighted by Courtney Bohannon 3-pointer with 2:07 left in the game. That was Bohannon's only points of the game. Moraye Ivy hit a runner in the lane with 52 seconds left, giving Tennessee State the lead, 48-47. For the game, Tennessee State from the field shot 17-of-47 for 36 percent, while Towson State was 14-of-57 for 25 percent. After Tennessee State built its largest lead of the game at 32-25 with 15:50 left in the game, Towson State went on a 9-0 run and did not allow a field goal for the next 7:14. Towson State was outrebounded 46-37. Weaver scored 10 first-half points. After Tennessee State jumped to a 7-2 advantage, neither team built a larger lead than four points as Towson State led 25-24 at halftime.
